organization.description: The GIS Support and Research Facility is a public computing facility established to support the use of geographic information system (GIS) technology at Iowa State University. The mission of the facility is to provide a high level GIS research support laboratory for students, faculty and staff as well as to provided GIS education and outreach to the ISU community and the state of Iowa.

name: air-emission-points-for-facilities-in-iowa-with-operating-permits-for-title-v-of-the-federal-cl
notes: Air emission points for facilities in Iowa with operating permits for Title V of the Federal Clean Air Act, considered "major" permits. Also includes emission points for a few facilities that are considered minor, but must have a Title V operating permit for part of their operation. Includes some stack parameters.
